cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM 

This paper deals with creative image generation, specifically in the domain of cartoon sketches. The paper discusses the use of GANs and mathematical transformations to create variations in the drawings. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and graphics (cs.GR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of domain-specific knowledge and the application of these tools in design processes, which suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the application of these tools in textiles, graphics, architectural elements, and interior design, which falls under the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
